{"name": "pyxid2", "metadata": {"name": "pyxid2", "version": "1.0.8", "classifiers": ["Intended Audience :: Developers", "License :: OSI Approved :: BSD License", "Operating System :: MacOS :: MacOS X", "Operating System :: Microsoft :: Windows", "Operating System :: POSIX", "Programming Language :: Python", "Topic :: System :: Hardware"], "home_page": "http://www.github.com/cedrus-opensource/pyxid/", "license": "BSD", "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": ["ftd2xx"], "summary": "Python library for interfacing with Cedrus XID devices, e.g. StimTracker, Riponda, RB-x40, c-pod, and Lumina.", "upload_time": 1732648040}, "documentation": ["Python library for communicating with all Cedrus XID devices: StimTracker, RB-x40 response pads, c-pod, Lumina, and SV-1.\r\n\r\nXID (eXperiment Interface Device) devices are used with software such as SuperLab, Presentation, and E-Prime for receiving input as part of stimulus/response testing experiments. This handles all of the low level device handling for XID devices in python projects.\r\n\r\nMinimal samples for collecting responses and sending event markers are available in the Git repo.\r\n\r\n------\r\nResponse collection in pyxid\r\n\r\nWhen a physical key is pressed on the device, a set of bytes describing it go into the serial buffer. This also occurs when the physical key is released. Calling poll_for_response() makes pyxid check the serial buffer for bytes constituting a response packet, and put a response object in its internal response queue. It does so once per poll_for_response() call. Calling get_next_response() pops a single response from the response queue. If you want to avoid seeing more responses than necessary, you can use flush_serial_buffer() to prevent more responses from being added to the queue by poll_for_response(), and you can clear already processed responses with clear_response_queue().\r\n\r\nThe response object is a python dict with the following keys:\r\n\r\n    port: Device port the response was from (typically 0)\r\n    key: Response pad key pressed by the subject\r\n    pressed: True if the key was pressed, False if it was released\r\n    time: value of the Response Time timer when the key was pressed/released\r\n\r\nFor an example see sample/responses.py\r\n\r\n------\r\nSending a TTL pulse signal via the library can be done via the following methods:\r\n\r\n    set_pulse_duration()\r\n    activate_line()\r\n    clear_line()\r\n    clear_all_lines()\r\n\r\nFor an example see sample/event_markers.py\r\n\r\n------\r\nTimers\r\n\r\nEach XID device has an internal timer. This timer can be reset via reset_timer() or automatically on the onset of a light sensor or onset of audio. It's commonplace to reset the timer at the start of the experiment and/or at the onset of a simulus.\r\n"], "modules": [{"name": "pyxid2.constants", "documentation": ["-*- coding: utf-8 -*-"], "functions": [], "variables": [{"name": "pyxid2.constants.KEY_RELEASE_BITMASK", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "pyxid2.constants.INVALID_PORT_BITS", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "pyxid2.constants.XID_PACKET_SIZE", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "pyxid2.constants.ST2_PACKET_SIZE", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "pyxid2.keymaps", "documentation": ["-*- coding: utf-8 -*-"], "functions": [], "variables": [{"name": "pyxid2.keymaps.rb_530_keymap", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "pyxid2.keymaps.rb_730_keymap", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "pyxid2.keymaps.rb_830_keymap", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "pyxid2.keymaps.rb_834_keymap", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "pyxid2.keymaps.lumina_keymap", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "pyxid2", "documentation": ["-*- coding: utf-8 -*-"], "functions": [{"name": "pyxid2.get_xid_devices", "asynchronous": false, "params": [], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Returns a list of all Xid devices connected to your computer."]}, {"name": "pyxid2.get_xid_device", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "device_number", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "variables": [{"name": "pyxid2.scanner", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "pyxid2.internal", "documentation": ["-*- coding: utf-8 -*-"], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [{"name": "pyxid2.internal.XidConnection", "bases": ["object"], "methods": [{"name": "pyxid2.internal.XidConnection.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "ftd2xx_index", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "baud_rate", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "pyxid2.internal.XidConnection.set_using_stim_tracker_output", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "using_st", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "pyxid2.internal.XidConnection.set_resp_packet_size", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "st2_packet_size", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "pyxid2.internal.XidConnection.clear_digital_output_lines", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "lines", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "leave_remaining_lines", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "pyxid2.internal.XidConnection.set_digital_output_lines", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "lines", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "leave_remaining_lines", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "pyxid2.internal.XidConnection.set_digio_lines_to_mask", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "lines", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "pyxid2.internal.XidConnection.flush", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "mask", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "pyxid2.internal.XidConnection.open", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "pyxid2.internal.XidConnection.close", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "pyxid2.internal.XidConnection.send_xid_command", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "command", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "bytes_expected", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "pyxid2.internal.XidConnection.send_xid_byte_command", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "command", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "bytes_expected", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "pyxid2.internal.XidConnection.read", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "bytes_to_read", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "pyxid2.internal.XidConnection.set_timeout", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "timeout", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "pyxid2.internal.XidConnection.write", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "command", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "pyxid2.internal.XidConnection.write_bytes", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "command", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "pyxid2.internal.XidConnection.check_for_keypress", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "pyxid2.internal.XidConnection.xid_input_found", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "pyxid2.internal.XidConnection.st2_input_found", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "pyxid2.internal.XidConnection.get_current_response", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["reads the current response data from the object and returns\nit in a dict.\n\nCurrently 'time' is reported as 0 until clock drift issues are\nresolved."]}], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": []}], "exports": []}, {"name": "pyxid2.pyxid_impl", "documentation": ["-*- coding: utf-8 -*-"], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [{"name": "pyxid2.pyxid_impl.XidScanner", "bases": ["object"], "methods": [{"name": "pyxid2.pyxid_impl.XidScanner.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "pyxid2.pyxid_impl.XidScanner.detect_xid_devices", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["For all of the com ports connected to the computer, send an\nXID command '_c1'.  If the device response with '_xid', it is\nan xid device."]}, {"name": "pyxid2.pyxid_impl.XidScanner.device_at_index", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "index", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Returns the device at the specified index"]}, {"name": "pyxid2.pyxid_impl.XidScanner.device_count", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Number of XID devices connected to the computer"]}], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": ["Scan the computer for connected XID devices"]}, {"name": "pyxid2.pyxid_impl.XidError", "bases": ["Exception"], "methods": [], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": []}, {"name": "pyxid2.pyxid_impl.XidDevice", "bases": ["object"], "methods": [{"name": "pyxid2.pyxid_impl.XidDevice.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "xid_connection", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "pyxid2.pyxid_impl.XidDevice.__del__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "pyxid2.pyxid_impl.XidDevice.reset_timer", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Resets the timer."]}, {"name": "pyxid2.pyxid_impl.XidDevice.query_timer", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Gets the value from the device's timer"]}, {"name": "pyxid2.pyxid_impl.XidDevice.reset_rt_timer", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "pyxid2.pyxid_impl.XidDevice.reset_base_timer", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "pyxid2.pyxid_impl.XidDevice.query_base_timer", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "pyxid2.pyxid_impl.XidDevice.is_response_device", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["\"Response device\" is used loosely here. Second generation StimTrackers are not response\ndevices in a strict sense, but they are capable of reporting keypresses via USB.\nThe only devices you will never get a keypress from are first gen StimTrackers and c-pods."]}, {"name": "pyxid2.pyxid_impl.XidDevice.init_device", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Initializes the device with the proper keymaps and name"]}, {"name": "pyxid2.pyxid_impl.XidDevice._send_command", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "command", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "expected_bytes", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Send an XID command to the device"]}, {"name": "pyxid2.pyxid_impl.XidDevice.poll_for_response", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Polls the device for user input\n\nIf there is a keymapping for the device, the key map is applied\nto the key reported from the device. This only applies to port 0\n(typically the physical buttons) responses. Rest are unchanged.\n\nIf a response is waiting to be processed, the response is appended\nto the internal response_queue"]}, {"name": "pyxid2.pyxid_impl.XidDevice.response_queue_size", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Number of responses in the response queue"]}, {"name": "pyxid2.pyxid_impl.XidDevice.has_response", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Do we have responses in the queue"]}, {"name": "pyxid2.pyxid_impl.XidDevice.get_next_response", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Pops the response at the beginning of the response queue\nand returns it.\n\nThis function returns a dict object with the following keys:\n\n    pressed:  A boolean value of whether the event was a keypress\n              or key release.\n    key:      The key on the device that was pressed.  This is a\n              0 based index.\n    port:     Device port the response came from.  Typically this\n              is 0 on RB-series devices, and 2 on SV-1 voice key\n              devices.\n    time:     For the time being, this just returns 0.  There is\n              currently an issue with clock drift in the Cedrus XID\n              devices.  Once we have this issue resolved, time will\n              report the value of the RT timer in miliseconds."]}, {"name": "pyxid2.pyxid_impl.XidDevice.clear_response_queue", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Clears the response queue"]}, {"name": "pyxid2.pyxid_impl.XidDevice.flush_serial_buffer", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "mask", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Will flush both input and output buffers by default.", "1 is output (from device) only, 2 is input (to device) only"]}, {"name": "pyxid2.pyxid_impl.XidDevice.set_pulse_duration", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "duration", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Sets the pulse duration for events in miliseconds when activate_line\nis called"]}, {"name": "pyxid2.pyxid_impl.XidDevice.get_pulse_duration", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "pyxid2.pyxid_impl.XidDevice.activate_line", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "lines", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "bitmask", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "leave_remaining_lines", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Triggers an output line.\n\nThere are up to 16 output lines on XID devices that can be raised\nin any combination.  To raise lines 1 and 7, for example, you pass\nin the list: activate_line(lines=[1, 7]).\n\nTo raise a single line, pass in just an integer, or a list with a\nsingle element to the lines keyword argument:\n\n    activate_line(lines=3)\n\n    or\n\n    activate_line(lines=[3])\n\nThe `lines` argument must either be an Integer, list of Integers, or\nNone.\n\nIf you'd rather specify a bitmask for setting the lines, you can use\nthe bitmask keyword argument.  Bitmask must be a Integer value between\n0 and 255 where 0 specifies no lines, and 255 is all lines.  For a\nmapping between lines and their bit values, see the `_lines` class\nvariable.\n\nTo use this, call the function as so to activate lines 1 and 6:\n\n    activate_line(bitmask=33)\n\nleave_remaining_lines tells the function to only operate on the lines\nspecified.  For example, if lines 1 and 8 are active, and you make\nthe following function call:\n\n    activate_line(lines=4, leave_remaining_lines=True)\n\nThis will result in lines 1, 4 and 8 being active.\n\nIf you call activate_line(lines=4) with leave_remaining_lines=False\n(the default), if lines 1 and 8 were previously active, only line 4\nwill be active after the call."]}, {"name": "pyxid2.pyxid_impl.XidDevice.clear_line", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "lines", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "bitmask", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "leave_remaining_lines", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["The inverse of activate_line.  If a line is active, it deactivates it.\n\nThis has the same parameters as activate_line()"]}, {"name": "pyxid2.pyxid_impl.XidDevice.set_lines", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "lines", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "pyxid2.pyxid_impl.XidDevice.clear_all_lines", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "pyxid2.pyxid_impl.XidDevice.save_to_flash", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "pyxid2.pyxid_impl.XidDevice.get_single_shot", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "selector", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["'_ia'", "Example: get_single_shot('K')"]}, {"name": "pyxid2.pyxid_impl.XidDevice.set_single_shot", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "selector", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "action", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "delay", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["'ia'", "Example: set_single_shot('K', True, 150)"]}, {"name": "pyxid2.pyxid_impl.XidDevice.get_signal_filter", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "selector", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["'_if'", "Example: get_signal_filter('K')"]}, {"name": "pyxid2.pyxid_impl.XidDevice.set_signal_filter", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "selector", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "holdOn", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "holdOff", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["'if'", "Example: set_signal_filter('K', 100, 200)"]}, {"name": "pyxid2.pyxid_impl.XidDevice.get_enable_digital_output", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "selector", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["'_io'", "Example: get_enable_digital_output('M')"]}, {"name": "pyxid2.pyxid_impl.XidDevice.set_enable_digital_output", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "selector", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "enable", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["'io'", "Example: set_enable_digital_output('M', False)"]}, {"name": "pyxid2.pyxid_impl.XidDevice.get_enable_usb_output", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "selector", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["'_iu'", "Example: get_enable_usb_output('M')"]}, {"name": "pyxid2.pyxid_impl.XidDevice.set_enable_usb_output", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "selector", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "enable", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["'iu'", "Example: set_enable_usb_output('M', False)"]}, {"name": "pyxid2.pyxid_impl.XidDevice.is_input_paused", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["'_ip'", "Example: is_input_paused()"]}, {"name": "pyxid2.pyxid_impl.XidDevice.pause_output", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "pause", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["'ip'", "Example: pause_output(True)"]}, {"name": "pyxid2.pyxid_impl.XidDevice.get_pulse_table_bitmask", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "pyxid2.pyxid_impl.XidDevice.set_pulse_table_bitmask", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "mask", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "pyxid2.pyxid_impl.XidDevice.clear_pulse_table", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "pyxid2.pyxid_impl.XidDevice.is_pulse_table_running", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "pyxid2.pyxid_impl.XidDevice.run_pulse_table", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "pyxid2.pyxid_impl.XidDevice.stop_pulse_table", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "pyxid2.pyxid_impl.XidDevice.add_pulse_table_entry", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "time", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "mask", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "pyxid2.pyxid_impl.XidDevice.reset_output_lines", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "pyxid2.pyxid_impl.XidDevice.__getattr__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "attrname", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "pyxid2.pyxid_impl.XidDevice.__str__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "pyxid2.pyxid_impl.XidDevice.__repr__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "def